Although behavioral and technological interventions can result in some modest improvements in glycemic control , these interventions did not fare significantly better than usual care in achieving glycemic control .
The follow-up rate after 5 years was 85%.
This means that the maturation of calluses was 27% faster in the LIPUS group.

While behavioral and technological interventions can lead to some modest improvements in glycemic control, these interventions have not performed much better than conventional prevention in achieving glycemic control.
